You can use grep command to count the number of times "mauris" appears in the file as shown.
  $ grep -o -i mauris example.txt | wc -l
  
  
  Find and replace text within a file using sed command
  sed -i 's/old-text/new-text/g' input.txt
  
  head by default prints 10 line
 $ head -n 5 state.txt
Andhra Pradesh
Arunachal Pradesh
Assam
Bihar
Chhattisgarh


Without any option it display only the last 10 lines of the file specified.
Example:

$ tail state.txt

$ tail -3 state.txt   last 3 lines prints
